### Installation

First, configure the build:

    perl Makefile.PL

If you want to install under your home directory, set the prefix accordingly:

    perl Makefile.PL PREFIX=~

If you're installing to your home directory, you'll probably want to fix up the
perl's library path, as shown below:

    export PERL5LIB=$HOME/share/perl5

Once the build is configured, the process continues as usual:

    make
    make test
    make install

